name: Chicken Biryani
instructions: Marinate chicken with yogurt and spices. Fry onions until golden. Cook marinated chicken separately. Half-cook rice, layer with chicken, and dum-cook with ghee. Serve hot.

name: Paneer Butter Masala
instructions: Sauté onions in butter, add tomatoes, cook well. Blend to make smooth gravy. Add spices, paneer, and cream. Simmer for 5 mins and serve with naan or rice.

name: Masala Dosa
instructions: Soak and grind rice and dal, ferment overnight. Cook mashed potatoes with spices. Make dosa on a hot pan, fill with potato stuffing, and serve with chutney and sambar.

name: Chole Bhature
instructions: Cook chickpeas with tomatoes and spices. Make soft dough with flour and yogurt, roll into puris, and deep fry. Serve hot with chole.

name: Gulab Jamun
instructions: Make dough with milk powder, flour, ghee, and baking soda. Shape into small balls and deep fry. Boil sugar syrup with cardamom. Soak fried balls in syrup and serve warm.
